What you need to know:

World Athletics President supports the use of new methodsUgandan Joshua Cheptegei (men's 10,000m) and Ethiopia's Letesenbet Gidey (women's 5,000m) blew two longstanding records apart in Valencia.Both athletes had a team of metronomic pacemakers around them who utilised Wavelight technology - a trackside visual time guidance system which lights up to indicate the world record pace.